Classification.Comment: This 11p duplication contains multiple protein-coding genes including H19, IGF2, KCNQ1 and CDKN1C. While paternal duplications are associated with the Beckwith-Wiedemann (BWS) syndrome (OMIM 130650) and an elevated risk for Wilms tumor-2 (OMIM 194071), maternal duplications involving the same region are associated with the Silver-Russell syndrome (SRS) (OMIM 180860). Therefore, this copy number variant is classified as pathogenic.
